tool_description: Get information about the OutSystems community. This is not an official OutSystems API.
title: OutSystems Community API

api_list.name: get_profiles

optional_parameters.name: sort_by
optional_parameters.description: String (desc, asc). Orders the results by either Ascending or Descending order.

optional_parameters.name: order_by
optional_parameters.description: String (name, rank, kudos, components, solutions, profile_score, training_score, forums_score, forge_score, ideas_score, total_score, forums_posts, forums_comments, ideas_submitted, ideas_commented, forge_components, publications_articles, certifications). Sorts the results by chosen value.

optional_parameters.name: page
optional_parameters.description: Used to see the next page of profiles, eg limit=15 and page=2 will show you profiles 15-30

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: The limit of results per page that has been set. Integer between 1 - 50 (inclusive)

optional_parameters.name: keyword
optional_parameters.description: Search keyword against profile name, job title, company or location.

profiles.name: Miguel 'Kelter' Antunes
profiles.description:
Like my components? Buy me a beer :) and support my work. 


About me I've been in web development environment for 10 years and I'm passionate about technology and innovation. I consider myself as a web performance maniac. In some of my spare time I like to work on software projects, exploring and learning state-of-the-art technologies. That along with enjoying life by traveling with my lovely girl and then edit travel footage into youtube videos, playing computer and mobile games and most recently I discovered the aquascaping hobby. As Web Developer on my daily basis I use Javascript, jQuery, HTML5, CSS, Rest APIs, Bootstrap, C#, SQL, OutSystems. I'm open minded to all technologies with great ability to learn and effectively use them.

I can switch between OutSystems, .NET and Java and back again like few people that I know of.
Despite my strong technical side, I do care very much for simplicity and user experience, which are present in my every work.

profiles.name: Caio Santana Magalhães
profiles.description:
Fullstack developer working professionally exclusively with OutSystems technologies since 2015. Currently working as an OutSystems Consultant at Digital Alchimia (São Paulo - Brazil) taking the roles of Senior OutSystems Developer and Tech Lead.

Began working with the Platform Version 9 during an initiative of migrating legacy PHP systems onto OutSystems and did not stop ever since. Through Digital Alchimia, contributed to customers (both from Brazil and international ones) in the fields of Telecommunications, Human Resources, Auditing, Insurance, Retail Business and more.

I enthusiastically follow the advancements and new features released on the Platform over the years, always packed with fresh and exciting technologies such as Reactive Web/Mobile Applications (that are as easy to build as ever!), and the new AI-oriented features.

I am especially fond of the Forge initiative. Ever since the beginning, I have been releasing Forge components and improving existing ones as a way of contributing with our thriving community.

profiles.name: Jorge Martins
profiles.description:
I taught at the University of Lisbon for over 13 years, from courses on programming fundamentals to advanced courses on software engineering, testing and advanced programming paradigms.

Since late 2014 I have been working at/with OutSystems, both developing applications, designing and developing the training experience and certifications and delivering training.

Recognised by OutSystems as one of their Most Valuable Professionals (MVP) since 2018, I've been an active member of the community, helping organize user group events in Singapore and Jakarta, talking at OutSystems Conferences and generally lending a helping hand on the forums as much as possible.

We started ITUp with the vision: "Be the leader creating highly qualified OutSystems Professionals". Our approach is based on pluggable training modules associated with hands-on training. The programs are designed for all kinds of IT skill levels, from no experience (typically with a STEM background), to experienced web developers in different technologies, like .NET or Java - whom we convert into OutSystems Developers.

profiles.name: Rafael Fantato
profiles.description:
7 years experience with OutSystems: pre-sales, senior dev, tech lead and training (Professional Web, Mobile, and Tech Lead Certified).

Over the last decade, I worked in IT, including management and development of web and mobile projects, architecture, prototypes, gathering requirements, business analysis, and innovation area finding new techs to the projects.

In 2015 I worked in a startup accelerator in New York / USA (Food-X) with mentoring and support for product development for 4 months, focusing on management, productivity, engagement, and entrepreneurship.

My most recently experience has been in web and mobile projects, sensory rooms, virtual receptions, VR360, games, totems, and corporate museums, for clients such as JHSF, CET, Nestle, Unilever, BMW-Motorrad, Senac, Editora Abril, Petrobras and Odebrecht , this being working in the development and implantation of the museums of São Paulo, Salvador and Lima / Perú.

I also worked as strategic planning, digital marketing and social monitoring with experience in CRM and Social Media for clients such as BMW-Motorrad, Vale and EBX with development of integrations with API's for instant notifications and alerts for the communication area.

Knowledge in Backend, Creative Frontend (HTML5 / CSS3 / jQuery), Bootstrap, Processing, Java, Adobe Air. Maintenance in systems in Python / Web2Py, C #, .NET, GoogleAppEngine and Amazon AWS, portals, websites and e-commerce.

Because Outsystems is so versatile and rapid I can have results either during the business meeting or quickly after that. This makes sure that the WOW factor is large which makes it easier for the app owner to "sell" his idea.
